Company Description
Structube wants to offer its clients a wide range of modern edge home furniture at its best affordable prices! We help our customers rediscover their home, one room at a time. With over 80 stores nationwide and over 700 employees and counting, Structube's small family business has become a thriving retailer brand looking to transform its future retail markets. Join Structube and come experience working with our ambitious, dynamic and motivating team!.
Job Description
We are looking for a BI Analyst who, reporting to the Logistics Director, will work to develop and improve tools supporting the operations of the company.
Job description:
Develop BI tools and reports using technologies such as: PowerBI, SSRS and Crystal Report, PowerApps;
Develop and update SQL and T-SQL queries;
Develop, test and modify the logics of the WMS system (C #);
Set up SSIS solutions to automate data entry and extraction tasks;
Produce ad hoc analyzes;
Support users of WMS and ERP systems at certain levels;
Participate in system updates: Developments, Tests, Training, Setup and support.
Qualifications
BAC or DEC in engineering or computer science;
Master the environment of MS SQL Server and T-SQL;
Expert to analyze data on Excel;
Knowledge of a programming language (C #, VBA, JAVA, PHYTON);
Experience in a distribution environment or WMS systems;
Knowledge of Power BI and DAX, NAV or Business central is an asset;
Bilingualism (French and English).
Additional Information
WE OFFER YOU
Flexible hours, massage room, coffee and activities with colleagues, etc.
Group insurance starting six months after hiring.
Virtual Healthcare, stress management and well-being service;
On-site parking and free electric cars charging stations.
Various corporative discounts (gym, telecommunications, etc.).
25% discount on all Structube items.
A collaborative and solutions-oriented work environment.
Dream a space for them. Dream a career for you at Structube!
